reviews.text: What has happened to the pond in the upside garden since the new lifts and bridge have arrived? It happens to have gone back to the 1920,s and should have been heritage listed....

Never usually use trains and never will again after today! Train never turned up, staff very unhelpful. Had to pay another £66 for another ticket! If government think people will use trains instead of cars they are absolutely deluded!

First Class Country Station, Bathrooms, Cafe & Staff; that are friendly. Clean & well looked after. Well serviced for London & Plymouth; also services to the north of the country. Expensive parking, but very cheap bus services. Departure Boards & Tannoy Announcements. A short Walk into town, a supermarket close by if you want snacks for your journey, did not notice a close at hand pub.

Dreadful station management, car ticket machine was not working properly with the card. Asked in the ticket office for help and told to ring the number, stated train was on the platform and about to leave, he just laughed!!!!
